### Autorização: Configuração Spatie + Inertia

#### [MODIFY] [app/Http/Middleware/HandleInertiaRequests.php](file://wsl.localhost/Ubuntu/var/www/app-agendamento/app/Http/Middleware/HandleInertiaRequests.php)

Compartilhar roles e permissions no Inertia global share:

```php
'auth' => [
    'user'        => $request->user(),
    'roles'       => $request->user()?->getRoleNames(),
    'permissions' => $request->user()?->getAllPermissions()->pluck('name'),
],
```

#### [NEW] `app/Http/Middleware/EnsureRole.php` (opcional, já existe via Spatie)

O Spatie registra automaticamente os middlewares `role` e `permission` no Laravel 11.

#### Uso nas rotas (exemplo)

```php
// routes/web.php
Route::middleware(['auth', 'role:profissional|admin'])->group(function () {
    Route::get('/dashboard', [DashboardController::class, 'index']);
});

Route::middleware(['auth', 'permission:gerenciar-servicos'])->group(function () {
    Route::resource('/servicos', ServicoController::class);
});
```

#### Uso no Vue/Inertia (exemplo)

```javascript
// composable: useAuth.js
import { usePage } from '@inertiajs/vue3'

export function useAuth() {
  const page = usePage()
  const permissions = computed(() => page.props.auth.permissions ?? [])
  const roles = computed(() => page.props.auth.roles ?? [])
  
  const can = (permission) => permissions.value.includes(permission)
  const is  = (role)       => roles.value.includes(role)
  
  return { can, is }
}

// Uso em componente Vue:
const { can, is } = useAuth()
// Ocultar botão:
// v-if="can('gerenciar-servicos')"
// v-if="is('admin')"
```

